      "code": "4.2",
      "title": "Work packages, activities, resources and timing",
      "description": "Group your activities into work packages. A work package means a major sub-division of the project.\n\nFor each work package, enter an objective (expected outcome) and list the activities, milestones and deliverables that belong to it.\n\nProjects should normally have a minimum of 2 work packages. WP1 should cover the management and coordination activities. WP2 and further WPs should be used for the other project activities. The last WP should be dedicated to Impact and dissemination.\n\nWork packages covering financial support to third parties only allowed if authorised in the Call document/Programme Guide.\n\nEnter each activity/milestone/output/outcome/deliverable only once (under one work package).\n\nThe Coordinator remains fully responsible for the coordination tasks, even if they are delegated to someone else. Coordinator tasks cannot be subcontracted.",
      "general_context": null,
      "connects_from": null,
